page.title: 11TRANSPORT IN KEYINGHAM
page.content: Public and private bus services run through both villages, regularly everyday. The private bus company, Conor and Graham, operates between Hull and Easington, and serves some villages that are not on the public route. The public bus company, East Yorkshire Motor Company, operates between Hull and Withersea with a more frequent service but is slightly more expersive. The majority of people commute around the area by motor car, lorries (heavy goods vehicles) are used for transporting goods. Motor bikes of varying sizes are also used for personal transport as to bicycles, although these are mainly ridden for pleasure.
